♦ SMTP Enumeration (Metasploit)

Simple mail Transfer Protocol → 25, 465, 587 (Standard ports, 465/587 often for SSL/TLS)
ifconfig → 192.108.85.2                      # Your local IP address
target IP → 192.108.85.3                     # The target machine's IP address

→ service postgresql Start                   # Start the required database service for Metasploit
→ msfconsole                                 # Start the Metasploit Framework console

♦ Metasploit Configuration
→ workspace -a SMTP_Enum                     # Create and switch to a Metasploit workspace
→ setg RHOSTS 192.108.85.3                   # Globally set the target IP (RHOSTS)
→ setg RHOST 192.108.85.3                    # Globally set the target IP (RHOST)

♦ SMTP Version Scanning
→ Search type:auxiliary name:smtp            # Search for SMTP-related auxiliary modules
→ Use auxiliary/scanner/smtp/smtp_version    # Load the SMTP version scanner module
→ Show options                               # View required options
→ run                                        # Execute the module

♦ SMTP User Enumeration (smb_enum)
→ Search smtp-enum                           # Search for the specific user enumeration module
→ Use auxiliary/scanner/smtp/smtp_enum       # Load the SMTP user enumeration module
→ Show options                               # View required options
→ run                                        # Execute the module
